Source: nssbackup
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: NSsbackup team <nssbackup-team@lists.launchpad.net>
Uploaders: Jean-Peer Lorenz <peer.loz@gmx.net>, Ouattara Oumar Aziz (alias wattazoum) <wattazoum@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 5), python ( >= 2.5 ), python-setuptools, lsb-release
Standards-Version: 3.8.4

Package: nssbackup
Architecture: all
Depends: nssbackup-common(= ${binary:Version}),
   nssbackup-gtk(= ${binary:Version}),
Description: Not So Simple Backup Suite 
 NSsbackup is the successor of Sbackup intended for desktop
 use. It has multiuser support with nice handling of logs. It also has
 a plugin architecture that will allow you to extend its functionalities.

Package: nssbackup-common
Architecture: all
Depends: python ( >= 2.5 ),
Conflicts: sbackup
Description: NSsbackup Common files package
 NSsbackup common files package. This package contains the minimum set of
 files to make it run. It uses GIO/GVFS for access of remote backup
 destinations.

Package: nssbackup-gtk
Architecture: all
Depends: nssbackup-common(= ${binary:Version}),
         python ( >= 2.5 ),
         python-glade2,
         python-gtk2 (>= 2.10),
         python-gnome2,
         python-notify
Description: NSsbackup GTK+ GUI
 NSsbackup GTK+ GUI. This package installs the GTK+ GUI of NSsbackup
 including status indicator.

Package: nssbackup-plugins-fuse
Architecture: all
Depends: nssbackup-common(= ${binary:Version}),
         fuse-utils,
         curlftpfs,
         sshfs,
         python-pexpect
Description: NSsbackup Fuse FTP/SFTP plugin 
 NSsbackup plugins that use FUSE file systems. This package enables (optional)
 backups from and over FTP/SFTP/SSH locations using Fuse.

